main event: A civilian reported a sighting of an unidentified flying object in Colonia, New Jersey on March 26, 1969.
interesting points: The report lacks detailed information regarding the number of objects or lengths of observation., The sighting report was acknowledged by the Aerial Phenomena Office of Project Blue Book., No photographs or physical evidence were provided with the report., The witness expressed confusion about the experience in the handwritten statement., The conclusion of the report stated 'INSUFFICIENT DATA'.
witness description: Civilian individual who reported the sighting.
